<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n03009d"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n03" href="#n03009d">N03 (VI.B.3)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n03all.htm#n03009d"> 9(d)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> hymn ~</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"> On Easter Sunday St. Patrick went to Tara with his companions to receive audience of the King in his Hall of Justice. As he went along he chanted the beautiful <mark>hymn</mark>, which has become known as the &lsquo;Breastplate of St. Patrick,&rsquo; in order to protect himself and his followers from the dangers by which they were encompassed. <small> J.M. Flood, <a name="JMFI" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#JMFI"><cite title="source">Ireland: Its Saints and Scholars</cite></a> (n.d) 13</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
